Dube residents in Soweto are protesting this morning after being without electricity for at least six months. This after a transformer failure. They've now resorted to taking to the streets to vent their frustrations. Reporter @Slindelo_M is monitoring. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Residents of Dube in Soweto are demanding access to power after a transformer failed. The community has been without electricity for more than six months. READ: Soweto residents protest over power cuts They again took to the streets on Friday morning to voice their frustration. The residents have vowed to continue protesting until their power is restored. Eskom said while the transformer could have been replaced by now, the power utility has since discovered that customers had illegally installed a transformer and barred Eskom technicians from working in the area.